    <name>Music</name>
    <summary>Audio/video player with library</summary>
    <description>
        <p>A local library for audio and video (MVs), it can manage user playlists and filter by artists, albums, or singles</p>
        <p>This music player does not parse any metadata at all. It expects a library in the following format:</p>
        <p>> Library Folder</p>
        <p>>> M3U/M3U8 files for playlists</p>
        <p>>> Artist Folder</p>
        <p>>> Image for artist cover (will be used on subfiles without a cover)</p>
        <p>>>> Albums/Singles Folder</p>
        <p>>>>> Songs (example: "01 - name", "01. name" or just "name" if order is not important)</p>
        <p>>>>> Subfolders will also be parsed as singles/albums</p>
        <p>>>>> Image for album/single cover (will be used as artist cover if no artist specific cover)</p>
        <p>Some features:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Fast launching, loads covers after app is launched</li>
          <li>Artists view, albums view, singles view</li>
          <li>Animated covers and cover color themeing</li>
          <li>Run in background</li>
          <li>Adaptive UI and fullscreen mode</li>
          <li>Automatically distinguish albums and singles if a folder has less than 7 songs</li>
          <li>"All Songs", "Most Played" and "Recently Added" as default playlists</li>
          <li>All widgets representing files/folders can be dragged with the file path as the content</li>
          <li>Drop songs files into user created playlist to add them to playlist</li>
          <li>Drag and drop inside a playlist to rearrange it</li>
          <li>Rename and delete playlists</li>
          <li>Open files (requires filesystem host permission)</li>
          <li>MPRIS</li>
        </ul>
    </description>
